@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

    @{b}INTRODUCTION@{ub}

    Hello,
    this is a program like MonED (from Raul A. Sobon), but uses MUI instead.
    You can change the same parameters and much more.

    Additionally features:

    - @{b}Overscan@{ub} settings, that are not editable by Prefs/Overscan can
      be changed.
    - @{b}BeamCon0@{ub} settings could be changed.
    - some @{b}view parameters@{ub} can be changed.
    - you can call the @{b}functions@{ub} embedded in structures
      @{b}MonitorSpec/SpecialMonitor@{ub}.
      (but not MrgCop(), it crashes everytime ?)
    - changing of  @{b}Property-Flags@{ub} (useful for setting of WB-flag ?)
    - change or create @{b}Modename@{ub}

    @{b}All settings@{ub} can be resetted @{b}separately@{ub}, but it's also
    possible to @{b}reset@{ub} all @{b}together@{ub}.

    @{b}All settings@{ub} can be saved as @{b}icon tooltypes@{ub}.

    @{b}All settings@{ub} (yes, also the syncs) can be activated thru the
    enclosed programm @{b}MIPrefs@{ub} (earlier: @{b}ChangeHWOverscan@{ub}).
    This program reads all icons in @{b}DEVS:Monitors/@{ub} and activates the tooltypes
    it found therein.

    @{b}Please use the monitor drivers of Workbench 3.1.@{ub}
@endnode

